cked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 12, "created_at": "2017-10-26T07:21:01Z", "updated_at": "2018-10-28T18:58:57Z", "closed_at": "2018-10-28T18:58:57Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In our code (and in general), many file-open attempts are conditioned with something like `if os.path.exists`. For AutomagicIO to have any effect in such cases, one would need to patch any code to use `lexists` to be compatible with V5 annex repos. This seems unreasonable, hence I wonder if AutomagicIO should also make an attempt to acquire file content when `exists` is called on a file?\r\n\r\nIf that question get's a YES, we need to also consider `os.stat` at minimum.\r\n\r\nContinuing along these lines:\r\n\r\n- os.remove -> `datalad uninstall` for subdatasets,  `datalad remove` for files.\r\n- closing a file descriptor that is open for write -> `datalad add`\r\n- open an annex'ed file -> `datalad unlock` (originally suggested by @yarikoptic #1739, or maybe even @mih #1117)\r\n\r\nIf we do that, people would need to know next to nothing to get automatic data management in all their Python code.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_event